<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1354">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/156c.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Special Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi><note n="112" xml:id="d1354fn112">Same telegram to the Consuls at Chihuahua and Hermosillo. See
                                    also footnote 114.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-06">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Have been shown Associated Press dispatch stating that Villa is
                                anxious to have the Spanish Ambassador at Washington know that <pb facs="0907" n="791" xml:id="pg_791"/> Spaniards in Torreon may
                                expect no mercy. He is reported as requesting that the Ambassador be
                                advised that Spaniards had better get out while they can. Please see
                                Villa at once and say that the United States cannot believe that the
                                report is authentic but we feel compelled to protest in the most
                                emphatic terms against cruelty to foreigners whether Spaniards or
                                citizens of other countries. We are sure that Villa will on
                                reflection realize the importance of observing the rules of war and
                                respect the person and property of foreigners.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>